The paper discusses the analysis of social networks and interactions on online social networks, which falls under the category of social and information sciences. The paper specifically focuses on the analysis of pairwise interactions, which suggests that it may fall under the sub-category of social networks (cs.SOC) or social media (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of crawling public profiles and collecting data, which may fall under the sub-category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). The paper also discusses the use of interaction records to reveal real-life relationship intensities, which may fall under the sub-category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to analyze the collected data, which may fall under the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
